==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prejudicate
<hw>Pre*ju"di*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praejudicatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praejudicare</ets> to prejudge;
<ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>judicare</ets> to judge. See
<er>Judge</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed before due
examination.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Ignorance and <xex>prejudicate</xex>
opinions.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Biased by opinions formed prematurely;
prejudiced.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Prejudicate</xex> readers.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prejudicate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prejudicate
<hw>Pre*ju"di*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prejudicated</conjf>
